
                                  Fischland

 'Fischland' is derived from my experiences with Corel Draw 3.0 more than a
decade ago, Xfig and Adobe Illustrator introductions on the WWW.

 The name 'Fischland' is an area at the baltic sea, where I made the photo
that can be seen in the 'About' dialog. I think that the mamon gras and
sand dunes have much in common with vector graphics but I failed to come
with a short name illustrating this relation. So it's "Fischland", which
I guess will be strange enough to make it unique in our worlds limited
namespace.

o Ctrl: temporarily select the last used selection tool
  (selection, direct selection, group selection)
o Ctrl: toggle selection tool
o Shift+Click: Add to/Remove from selection

o Normally Illustrator styles a new object with the style of the last
  selected object


