Scaling factor
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
Vector coordinates are stored as integers, so a decision about the maximal
resolution has to be made. Other programs seem to use:

xfig       : 1200 dpi
illustrator: 9600 dpi

These numbers relate to common printer resolutions, ie. 75, 150, 300, 600,
1200, 2400, 4800 or 9600.

Papersize
^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
1cm = 0.394in
2.54cm = 1in 

NTSC: 525 - 43 retrace lines = 482 lines
VHS: 240
Terrestical: 330
Laserdisc: 425
DVD: 480
Satellite: 500


2.55:1
2.37:1
2.35:1 CinemaScope
1.85:1 = North America Movies, Academy Flat
1.78:1 = 16:9 = Widescreen TV and HDTV (1920x1080px)
1.66:1 Europe
1.33:1 = 4:3 = Academy Standard (Edison)

