selection tools

black arrow: selection
  select object as a whole (bounding box), move, rotate, scale
  - with alt: creates a copy and moves that
white arrow: direct selection
  select objects for manipulation of object points and paths
  - grabbing straight line segment moves line segment
  - grabbing bezier changes size but not angel so that the line
    intersects with the mouse
white arrow with +: group selection
  select an object within a group
lasso with black arrow: lasso
lasso with white arrow: direct lasso
CTRL+Click (Mac), Right Click (Windows)
  this one opens a popmenu, with
  Regroup
  Redo
  -------
  Zoom In
  Zoom Out
  --------
  Hide Rulers
  Show Grid
  Hide Guides
  Lock Guides
  ------
  Select
  ------
  Outline
  
  where Select opens:
  
  First Object Above
  Next Object Above
  First Object Below
  Next Object Below
  
  The entry Object in the menubar:
  
  Transform
  Arrange
  --------
  Group
  Ungroup
  Lock
  Unlock All
  Hide Selection
  Show All
  --------
  ...
  
  o Lock will make the currently selected object unselectables
  o Shift-Option-Command-2 (Mac), Shift-Option-Ctrl-2 (Win) 
    will lock all objects but the currently selected one
  o Hide will make an object invisible and unselectable
  
  

